-- Nigerian naira hit 3-month low, despite central bank intervention
-- By Oludare Mayowa
-- Wed Sep 17, 2014 10:12AM EDT
-- None



LAGOS, Sept 17 (Reuters) - Nigeria's naira <NGN=D1> fell 0.34 percent to a three-month closing low of 163.45 against the dollar on Wednesday, despite the central bank intervening for a second day to halt its slide, dealers said.

